How to measure your blood glucose levels 1

Testing your blood at home is quick and easy, although it can be uncomfortable. It does get better.

You would have been given:

  • a blood glucose metre
  • small needles called lancets
  • a plastic pen to hold the lancets
  • small test strips

Our Peer to Peer series explores the shared experience between GPs and other healthcare professionals working in a practice.

Our Peer to Peer episodes focus on the challenges.

I think what we're trying to do is learn from each other, learn from other practices, what practices do well, what we can offer them.

The rewards.

The beauty of general practice is that you can pretty much determine the career path you want to take.

And of course, the laughs.

I'm probably in love with you, but anyway.

It's been an interesting journey I think.

Watch or listen to the full episodes online now and to find out more about a career in general practice, search #ChooseGP.
